{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":88825,"duration_api_ms":88742,"num_turns":3,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"bd88a977-afd7-4b5d-931f-039a8da25294","total_cost_usd":0.31583155,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":23876,"cache_read_input_tokens":75666,"output_tokens":2550,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":23876,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":4,"outputTokens":2550,"cacheReadInputTokens":75666,"cacheCreationInputTokens":23876,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.250828,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":48,"outputTokens":3339,"cacheReadInputTokens":155118,"cacheCreationInputTokens":26199,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.06500355000000001,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"All three amendments identify real issues. Amendment 1 correctly flags that a contract violation is silently downgraded into a generic error. Amendment 2 asks for documentation of a deliberate spec deviation, which is low-risk and high-value for maintainability. Amendment 3 identifies a real race condition that can cause false CorruptRecord errors; while the exact fix mechanism needs design refinement, the regression test and the underlying issue are both valid.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-15-65fc1567","decision":"accept","rationale":"The contract violation (requested_run_id.is_some() && requested_started_at.is_none()) is a programming bug in a caller, yet it surfaces to operators as a generic 'no matching task run' error because the function returns None and the diagnostic information stays buried in a warn-level log line. The issue spec explicitly requires 'runtime checks that return errors in both debug and release builds.' Changing the return type to Result<Option<usize>, AppError> is the cleanest fix and correctly propagates the contract violation as a distinct error. At minimum, upgrading from warn to error is trivial, safe, and immediately improves observability for a condition that indicates a bug rather than a transient situation."},{"amendment_id":"fr-15-f8b418d4","decision":"accept","rationale":"The safe_plan_hash_backfill None branch already has a good comment explaining the ambiguity rationale, but neither the test nor the code explicitly notes that this is a deliberate deviation from Issue 3's acceptance criteria ('Lineage entries auto-populate plan_hash from the milestone snapshot when callers omit it'). Legacy open entries with snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation=None will never get backfilled even though a current snapshot exists. Adding a short comment in both locations referencing this as a known spec deviation is low-risk, prevents future reviewers from re-opening it as a regression, and costs nothing. This is purely a maintainability improvement."},{"amendment_id":"fr-15-994e9490","decision":"accept","rationale":"The race condition is real and mechanically reproducible: dispatch under plan v1 → persist_plan advances snapshot to v2 → record_task_run_start called without explicit plan_hash → entry gets stamped with v2 → finalization supplies the true v1 hash → CorruptRecord error fires with a false 'conflicting plan_hash' message. The code already documents this race in a comment (lines 3038-3043), which means the authors acknowledge it but haven't guarded against it. A regression test for the exact scenario (dispatch v1, advance snapshot, start without hash, complete with v1) is clearly needed to prevent this from being quietly closed as 'documented.' The broader fix — not stamping the snapshot hash when it cannot be verified to match the dispatched plan — requires caller-side cooperation (callers must pass plan_hash explicitly), but the amendment is correct that the storage layer should not silently assume the current snapshot matches the dispatched plan. Even if the full fix requires design work, accepting this amendment ensures the race is tested and tracked rather than just commented."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"3f112601-16a4-4421-9a5f-9cc7743d5c98"}
